Description: Floor sherd of Attic black glaze pottery cup-skyphos (?); interior glazed black with impressed decoration: from centre, part of palmette, circle of enclosed ovolos, alternately linked palmettes; underside: reserved with circles and wider bands in black glaze, partly fired brownish; inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1536)
